  <li><strong>Preheat oven.</strong> Preheat oven to 350Â°F and grease loaf pan.</li>
  <li><strong>Cream sugar &amp; butter.</strong> In a mixing bowl cream sugar and butter until smooth.</li>
  <li><strong>Add wet ingredients.</strong> Add eggs and blend. Measure and mix milk, vanilla, and sourdough starter.</li>
  <li><strong>Add dry ingredients.</strong> Measure and add nutmeg, cinnamon, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, and flour. Use electric mixer on low or whisk to blend. Do not overmix this stage.</li>
  <li><strong>Add to loaf pan.</strong> Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.</li>
  <li><strong>Bake.</strong> Bake for 45-50 minutes or until fork comes out mostly clean. Let sit for 10 minutes and then remove from pan.</li>
  <li><strong>Glaze.</strong> Once the loaf has cooled, pour 1 tbsp of lemon juice over top. Combine remaining glaze ingredients and spread on loaf. Top with lemon zest.</li>
